cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.PF, cs.SI, cs.DC

This paper deals with the analysis of Internet traffic and routing policies, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). It also discusses government enforced censorship and wiretapping, which are related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper uses BGP (Border Gateway Protocol) to analyze routing policies, which is a protocol used in network layer communication (cs.PF). The paper also deals with the AS-level topology and routing policies, which are related to system and information theory (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of national policies on international reachability, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
